111 CDriver::CDriver(char* confFile, unsigned short val_nZone, SU2_Comm MPICommunicator, bool dummy_geo) :
112  config_file_name(confFile), StartTime(0.0), StopTime(0.0), UsedTime(0.0),
113  TimeIter(0), nZone(val_nZone), StopCalc(false), fsi(false), fem_solver(false), dry_run(dummy_geo) {
114 
115  /*--- Initialize Medipack (must also be here so it is initialized from python) ---*/
116 #ifdef HAVE_MPI
117  #if defined(CODI_REVERSE_TYPE) || defined(CODI_FORWARD_TYPE)
118  SU2_MPI::Init_AMPI();
119  #endif
120 #endif
121 
122  SU2_MPI::SetComm(MPICommunicator);
123 
124  rank = SU2_MPI::GetRank();
125  size = SU2_MPI::GetSize();
126 
127  /*--- Start timer to track preprocessing for benchmarking. ---*/
128 
129  StartTime = SU2_MPI::Wtime();
130 
131  /*--- Initialize containers with null --- */
132 
133  SetContainers_Null();
134 
135  /*--- Preprocessing of the config files. ---*/
136 
137  Input_Preprocessing(config_container, driver_config);
138 
139  /*--- Retrieve dimension from mesh file ---*/
140 
141  nDim = CConfig::GetnDim(config_container[ZONE_0]->GetMesh_FileName(),
142  config_container[ZONE_0]->GetMesh_FileFormat());
143 
144  /*--- Output preprocessing ---*/
145 
146  Output_Preprocessing(config_container, driver_config, output_container, driver_output);
147 
148 
149  for (iZone = 0; iZone < nZone; iZone++) {
150 
151  /*--- Read the number of instances for each zone ---*/
152 
153  nInst[iZone] = config_container[iZone]->GetnTimeInstances();
154 
155  geometry_container[iZone] = new CGeometry** [nInst[iZone]] ();
156  iteration_container[iZone] = new CIteration* [nInst[iZone]] ();
157  solver_container[iZone] = new CSolver*** [nInst[iZone]] ();
158  integration_container[iZone] = new CIntegration** [nInst[iZone]] ();
159  numerics_container[iZone] = new CNumerics**** [nInst[iZone]] ();
160  grid_movement[iZone] = new CVolumetricMovement* [nInst[iZone]] ();
161 
162  /*--- Allocate transfer and interpolation container --- */
163 
164  interface_container[iZone] = new CInterface*[nZone] ();
165  interpolator_container[iZone].resize(nZone);
166 
167  for (iInst = 0; iInst < nInst[iZone]; iInst++) {
168 
169  config_container[iZone]->SetiInst(iInst);
170 
171  /*--- Preprocessing of the geometry for all zones. In this routine, the edge-
172  based data structure is constructed, i.e. node and cell neighbors are
173  identified and linked, face areas and volumes of the dual mesh cells are
174  computed, and the multigrid levels are created using an agglomeration procedure. ---*/
175 
176  Geometrical_Preprocessing(config_container[iZone], geometry_container[iZone][iInst], dry_run);
177 
178  }
179  }
180 
181  /*--- Before we proceed with the zone loop we have to compute the wall distances.
182  * This computation depends on all zones at once. ---*/
183  if (rank == MASTER_NODE)
184  cout << "Computing wall distances." << endl;
185 
186  CGeometry::ComputeWallDistance(config_container, geometry_container);
187 
188  for (iZone = 0; iZone < nZone; iZone++) {
189 
190  for (iInst = 0; iInst < nInst[iZone]; iInst++){
191 
192  /*--- Definition of the solver class: solver_container[#ZONES][#INSTANCES][#MG_GRIDS][#EQ_SYSTEMS].
193  The solver classes are specific to a particular set of governing equations,
194  and they contain the subroutines with instructions for computing each spatial
195  term of the PDE, i.e. loops over the edges to compute convective and viscous
196  fluxes, loops over the nodes to compute source terms, and routines for
197  imposing various boundary condition type for the PDE. ---*/
198 
199  Solver_Preprocessing(config_container[iZone], geometry_container[iZone][iInst], solver_container[iZone][iInst]);
200 
201  /*--- Definition of the numerical method class:
202  numerics_container[#ZONES][#INSTANCES][#MG_GRIDS][#EQ_SYSTEMS][#EQ_TERMS].
203  The numerics class contains the implementation of the numerical methods for
204  evaluating convective or viscous fluxes between any two nodes in the edge-based
205  data structure (centered, upwind, galerkin), as well as any source terms
206  (piecewise constant reconstruction) evaluated in each dual mesh volume. ---*/
207 
208  Numerics_Preprocessing(config_container[iZone], geometry_container[iZone][iInst],
209  solver_container[iZone][iInst], numerics_container[iZone][iInst]);
210 
211  /*--- Definition of the integration class: integration_container[#ZONES][#INSTANCES][#EQ_SYSTEMS].
212  The integration class orchestrates the execution of the spatial integration
213  subroutines contained in the solver class (including multigrid) for computing
214  the residual at each node, R(U) and then integrates the equations to a
215  steady state or time-accurately. ---*/
216 
217  Integration_Preprocessing(config_container[iZone], solver_container[iZone][iInst][MESH_0],
218  integration_container[iZone][iInst]);
219 
220  /*--- Instantiate the type of physics iteration to be executed within each zone. For
221  example, one can execute the same physics across multiple zones (mixing plane),
222  different physics in different zones (fluid-structure interaction), or couple multiple
223  systems tightly within a single zone by creating a new iteration class (e.g., RANS). ---*/
224 
225  Iteration_Preprocessing(config_container[iZone], iteration_container[iZone][iInst]);
226 
227  /*--- Dynamic mesh processing. ---*/
228 
229  DynamicMesh_Preprocessing(config_container[iZone], geometry_container[iZone][iInst], solver_container[iZone][iInst],
230  iteration_container[iZone][iInst], grid_movement[iZone][iInst], surface_movement[iZone]);
231 
232  /*--- Static mesh processing. ---*/
233 
234  StaticMesh_Preprocessing(config_container[iZone], geometry_container[iZone][iInst]);
235 
236  }
237 
238  }
239 
240  /*! --- Compute the wall distance again to correctly compute the derivatives if we are running direct diff mode --- */
241  if (driver_config->GetDirectDiff() == D_DESIGN){
242  CGeometry::ComputeWallDistance(config_container, geometry_container);
243  }
244 
245  /*--- Definition of the interface and transfer conditions between different zones. ---*/
246 
247  if (nZone > 1) {
248  if (rank == MASTER_NODE)
249  cout << endl <<"------------------- Multizone Interface Preprocessing -------------------" << endl;
250 
251  Interface_Preprocessing(config_container, solver_container, geometry_container,
252  interface_types, interface_container, interpolator_container);
253  }
254 
255  if (fsi) {
256  for (iZone = 0; iZone < nZone; iZone++) {
257  for (iInst = 0; iInst < nInst[iZone]; iInst++){
258  Solver_Restart(solver_container[iZone][iInst], geometry_container[iZone][iInst],
259  config_container[iZone], true);
260  }
261  }
262  }
263 
264  if (config_container[ZONE_0]->GetBoolTurbomachinery()){
265  if (rank == MASTER_NODE)
266  cout << endl <<"---------------------- Turbomachinery Preprocessing ---------------------" << endl;
267 
268  Turbomachinery_Preprocessing(config_container, geometry_container, solver_container, interface_container);
269  }
270 
271 
272  PythonInterface_Preprocessing(config_container, geometry_container, solver_container);
273 
274 
275  /*--- Preprocessing time is reported now, but not included in the next compute portion. ---*/
276 
277  StopTime = SU2_MPI::Wtime();
278 
279  /*--- Compute/print the total time for performance benchmarking. ---*/
280 
281  UsedTime = StopTime-StartTime;
282  UsedTimePreproc = UsedTime;
283  UsedTimeCompute = 0.0;
284  UsedTimeOutput = 0.0;
285  IterCount = 0;
286  OutputCount = 0;
287  MDOFs = 0.0;
288  MDOFsDomain = 0.0;
289  Mpoints = 0.0;
290  MpointsDomain = 0.0;
291  for (iZone = 0; iZone < nZone; iZone++) {
292  Mpoints += geometry_container[iZone][INST_0][MESH_0]->GetGlobal_nPoint()/(1.0e6);
293  MpointsDomain += geometry_container[iZone][INST_0][MESH_0]->GetGlobal_nPointDomain()/(1.0e6);
294  MDOFs += DOFsPerPoint*geometry_container[iZone][INST_0][MESH_0]->GetGlobal_nPoint()/(1.0e6);
295  MDOFsDomain += DOFsPerPoint*geometry_container[iZone][INST_0][MESH_0]->GetGlobal_nPointDomain()/(1.0e6);
296  }
297 
298  /*--- Reset timer for compute/output performance benchmarking. ---*/
299 
300  StopTime = SU2_MPI::Wtime();
301 
302  /*--- Compute/print the total time for performance benchmarking. ---*/
303 
304  UsedTime = StopTime-StartTime;
305  UsedTimePreproc = UsedTime;
306 
307  /*--- Reset timer for compute performance benchmarking. ---*/
308 
309  StartTime = SU2_MPI::Wtime();
310 
311 }
312 
313 void CDriver::SetContainers_Null(){
314 
315  /*--- Create pointers to all of the classes that may be used throughout
316  the SU2_CFD code. In general, the pointers are instantiated down a
317  hierarchy over all zones, multigrid levels, equation sets, and equation
318  terms as described in the comments below. ---*/
319 
320  ConvHist_file = nullptr;
321  iteration_container = nullptr;
322  output_container = nullptr;
323  integration_container = nullptr;
324  geometry_container = nullptr;
325  solver_container = nullptr;
326  numerics_container = nullptr;
327  config_container = nullptr;
328  surface_movement = nullptr;
329  grid_movement = nullptr;
330  FFDBox = nullptr;
331  interface_container = nullptr;
332  interface_types = nullptr;
333  nInst = nullptr;
334 
335  /*--- Definition and of the containers for all possible zones. ---*/
336 
337  iteration_container = new CIteration**[nZone] ();
338  solver_container = new CSolver****[nZone] ();
339  integration_container = new CIntegration***[nZone] ();
340  numerics_container = new CNumerics*****[nZone] ();
341  config_container = new CConfig*[nZone] ();
342  geometry_container = new CGeometry***[nZone] ();
343  surface_movement = new CSurfaceMovement*[nZone] ();
344  grid_movement = new CVolumetricMovement**[nZone] ();
345  FFDBox = new CFreeFormDefBox**[nZone] ();
346  interpolator_container.resize(nZone);
347  interface_container = new CInterface**[nZone] ();
348  interface_types = new unsigned short*[nZone] ();
349  output_container = new COutput*[nZone] ();
350  nInst = new unsigned short[nZone] ();
351  driver_config = nullptr;
352  driver_output = nullptr;
353 
354  for (iZone = 0; iZone < nZone; iZone++) {
355  interface_types[iZone] = new unsigned short[nZone];
356  nInst[iZone] = 1;
357  }
358 
359  strcpy(runtime_file_name, "runtime.dat");
360 
361 }

364 void CDriver::Postprocessing() {
365 
366  const bool wrt_perf = config_container[ZONE_0]->GetWrt_Performance();
367 
368  /*--- Output some information to the console. ---*/
369 
370  if (rank == MASTER_NODE) {
371 
372  /*--- Print out the number of non-physical points and reconstructions ---*/
373 
374  if (config_container[ZONE_0]->GetNonphysical_Points() > 0)
375  cout << "Warning: there are " << config_container[ZONE_0]->GetNonphysical_Points() << " non-physical points in the solution." << endl;
376  if (config_container[ZONE_0]->GetNonphysical_Reconstr() > 0)
377  cout << "Warning: " << config_container[ZONE_0]->GetNonphysical_Reconstr() << " reconstructed states for upwinding are non-physical." << endl;
378  }
379 
380  if (rank == MASTER_NODE)
381  cout << endl <<"------------------------- Solver Postprocessing -------------------------" << endl;
382 
383  for (iZone = 0; iZone < nZone; iZone++) {
384  for (iInst = 0; iInst < nInst[iZone]; iInst++){
385  Numerics_Postprocessing(numerics_container[iZone], solver_container[iZone][iInst],
386  geometry_container[iZone][iInst], config_container[iZone], iInst);
387  }
388  delete [] numerics_container[iZone];
389  }
390  delete [] numerics_container;
391  if (rank == MASTER_NODE) cout << "Deleted CNumerics container." << endl;
392 
393  for (iZone = 0; iZone < nZone; iZone++) {
394  for (iInst = 0; iInst < nInst[iZone]; iInst++){
395  Integration_Postprocessing(integration_container[iZone],
396  geometry_container[iZone][iInst],
397  config_container[iZone],
398  iInst);
399  }
400  delete [] integration_container[iZone];
401  }
402  delete [] integration_container;
403  if (rank == MASTER_NODE) cout << "Deleted CIntegration container." << endl;
404 
405  for (iZone = 0; iZone < nZone; iZone++) {
406  for (iInst = 0; iInst < nInst[iZone]; iInst++){
407  Solver_Postprocessing(solver_container[iZone],
408  geometry_container[iZone][iInst],
409  config_container[iZone],
410  iInst);
411  }
412  delete [] solver_container[iZone];
413  }
414  delete [] solver_container;
415  if (rank == MASTER_NODE) cout << "Deleted CSolver container." << endl;
416 
417  for (iZone = 0; iZone < nZone; iZone++) {
418  for (iInst = 0; iInst < nInst[iZone]; iInst++)
419  delete iteration_container[iZone][iInst];
420  delete [] iteration_container[iZone];
421  }
422  delete [] iteration_container;
423  if (rank == MASTER_NODE) cout << "Deleted CIteration container." << endl;
424 
425  if (interface_container != nullptr) {
426  for (iZone = 0; iZone < nZone; iZone++) {
427  if (interface_container[iZone] != nullptr) {
428  for (unsigned short jZone = 0; jZone < nZone; jZone++)
429  delete interface_container[iZone][jZone];
430  delete [] interface_container[iZone];
431  }
432  }
433  delete [] interface_container;
434  if (rank == MASTER_NODE) cout << "Deleted CInterface container." << endl;
435  }
436 
437  if (interface_types != nullptr) {
438  for (iZone = 0; iZone < nZone; iZone++)
439  delete [] interface_types[iZone];
440  delete [] interface_types;
441  }
442 
443  for (iZone = 0; iZone < nZone; iZone++) {
444  if (geometry_container[iZone] != nullptr) {
445  for (iInst = 0; iInst < nInst[iZone]; iInst++){
446  for (unsigned short iMGlevel = 0; iMGlevel < config_container[iZone]->GetnMGLevels()+1; iMGlevel++)
447  delete geometry_container[iZone][iInst][iMGlevel];
448  delete [] geometry_container[iZone][iInst];
449  }
450  delete [] geometry_container[iZone];
451  }
452  }
453  delete [] geometry_container;
454  if (rank == MASTER_NODE) cout << "Deleted CGeometry container." << endl;
455 
456  for (iZone = 0; iZone < nZone; iZone++) {
457  delete [] FFDBox[iZone];
458  }
459  delete [] FFDBox;
460  if (rank == MASTER_NODE) cout << "Deleted CFreeFormDefBox class." << endl;
461 
462  for (iZone = 0; iZone < nZone; iZone++) {
463  delete surface_movement[iZone];
464  }
465  delete [] surface_movement;
466  if (rank == MASTER_NODE) cout << "Deleted CSurfaceMovement class." << endl;
467 
468  for (iZone = 0; iZone < nZone; iZone++) {
469  for (iInst = 0; iInst < nInst[iZone]; iInst++)
470  delete grid_movement[iZone][iInst];
471  delete [] grid_movement[iZone];
472  }
473  delete [] grid_movement;
474  if (rank == MASTER_NODE) cout << "Deleted CVolumetricMovement class." << endl;
475 
476  /*--- Output profiling information ---*/
477  // Note that for now this is called only by a single thread, but all
478  // necessary variables have been made thread private for safety (tick/tock)!!
479 
480  config_container[ZONE_0]->SetProfilingCSV();
481  config_container[ZONE_0]->GEMMProfilingCSV();
482 
483  /*--- Deallocate config container ---*/
484  if (config_container!= nullptr) {
485  for (iZone = 0; iZone < nZone; iZone++)
486  delete config_container[iZone];
487  delete [] config_container;
488  }
489  delete driver_config;
490  if (rank == MASTER_NODE) cout << "Deleted CConfig container." << endl;
491 
492  delete [] nInst;
493  if (rank == MASTER_NODE) cout << "Deleted nInst container." << endl;
494 
495  /*--- Deallocate output container ---*/
496 
497  if (output_container!= nullptr) {
498  for (iZone = 0; iZone < nZone; iZone++)
499  delete output_container[iZone];
500  delete [] output_container;
501  }
502 
503  delete driver_output;
504 
505  if (rank == MASTER_NODE) cout << "Deleted COutput class." << endl;
506 
507  if (rank == MASTER_NODE) cout << "-------------------------------------------------------------------------" << endl;
508 
509 
510  /*--- Stop the timer and output the final performance summary. ---*/
511 
512  StopTime = SU2_MPI::Wtime();
513 
514  UsedTime = StopTime-StartTime;
515  UsedTimeCompute += UsedTime;
516 
517  if ((rank == MASTER_NODE) && (wrt_perf)) {
518  su2double TotalTime = UsedTimePreproc + UsedTimeCompute + UsedTimeOutput;
519  cout.precision(6);
520  cout << endl << endl <<"-------------------------- Performance Summary --------------------------" << endl;
521  cout << "Simulation totals:" << endl;
522  cout << setw(25) << "Wall-clock time (hrs):" << setw(12) << (TotalTime)/(60.0*60.0) << " | ";
523  cout << setw(20) << "Core-hrs:" << setw(12) << size*TotalTime/(60.0*60.0) << endl;
524  cout << setw(25) << "Cores:" << setw(12) << size << " | ";
525  cout << setw(20) << "DOFs/point:" << setw(12) << DOFsPerPoint << endl;
526  cout << setw(25) << "Points/core:" << setw(12) << 1.0e6*MpointsDomain/size << " | ";
527  cout << setw(20) << "Ghost points/core:" << setw(12) << 1.0e6*(Mpoints-MpointsDomain)/size << endl;
528  cout << setw(25) << "Ghost/Owned Point Ratio:" << setw(12) << (Mpoints-MpointsDomain)/MpointsDomain << " | " << endl;
529  cout << endl;
530  cout << "Preprocessing phase:" << endl;
531  cout << setw(25) << "Preproc. Time (s):" << setw(12)<< UsedTimePreproc << " | ";
532  cout << setw(20) << "Preproc. Time (%):" << setw(12)<< ((UsedTimePreproc * 100.0) / (TotalTime)) << endl;
533  cout << endl;
534  cout << "Compute phase:" << endl;
535  cout << setw(25) << "Compute Time (s):" << setw(12)<< UsedTimeCompute << " | ";
536  cout << setw(20) << "Compute Time (%):" << setw(12)<< ((UsedTimeCompute * 100.0) / (TotalTime)) << endl;
537  cout << setw(25) << "Iteration count:" << setw(12)<< IterCount << " | ";
538  if (IterCount != 0) {
539  cout << setw(20) << "Avg. s/iter:" << setw(12)<< UsedTimeCompute/IterCount << endl;
540  cout << setw(25) << "Core-s/iter/Mpoints:" << setw(12)<< size*UsedTimeCompute/IterCount/Mpoints << " | ";
541  cout << setw(20) << "Mpoints/s:" << setw(12)<< Mpoints*IterCount/UsedTimeCompute << endl;
542  } else cout << endl;
543  cout << endl;
544  cout << "Output phase:" << endl;
545  cout << setw(25) << "Output Time (s):" << setw(12)<< UsedTimeOutput << " | ";
546  cout << setw(20) << "Output Time (%):" << setw(12)<< ((UsedTimeOutput * 100.0) / (TotalTime)) << endl;
547  cout << setw(25) << "Output count:" << setw(12)<< OutputCount << " | ";
548  if (OutputCount != 0) {
549  cout << setw(20)<< "Avg. s/output:" << setw(12)<< UsedTimeOutput/OutputCount << endl;
550  if (BandwidthSum > 0) {
551  cout << setw(25)<< "Restart Aggr. BW (MB/s):" << setw(12)<< BandwidthSum/OutputCount << " | ";
552  cout << setw(20)<< "MB/s/core:" << setw(12)<< BandwidthSum/OutputCount/size << endl;
553  }
554  } else cout << endl;
555  cout << "-------------------------------------------------------------------------" << endl;
556  cout << endl;
557  }
558 
559  /*--- Exit the solver cleanly ---*/
560 
561  if (rank == MASTER_NODE)
562  cout << endl <<"------------------------- Exit Success (SU2_CFD) ------------------------" << endl << endl;
563 
564 }

615 void CDriver::Geometrical_Preprocessing(CConfig* config, CGeometry **&geometry, bool dummy){
616 
617  if (!dummy){
618  if (rank == MASTER_NODE)
619  cout << endl <<"------------------- Geometry Preprocessing ( Zone " << config->GetiZone() <<" ) -------------------" << endl;
620 
621  if( fem_solver ) {
622  switch( config->GetKind_FEM_Flow() ) {
623  case DG: {
624  Geometrical_Preprocessing_DGFEM(config, geometry);
625  break;
626  }
627  }
628  }
629  else {
630  Geometrical_Preprocessing_FVM(config, geometry);
631  }
632  } else {
633  if (rank == MASTER_NODE)
634  cout << endl <<"-------------------------- Using Dummy Geometry -------------------------" << endl;
635 
636  unsigned short iMGlevel;
637 
638  geometry = new CGeometry*[config->GetnMGLevels()+1] ();
639 
640  if (!fem_solver){
641  for (iMGlevel = 0; iMGlevel <= config->GetnMGLevels(); iMGlevel++) {
642  geometry[iMGlevel] = new CDummyGeometry(config);
643  }
644  } else {
645  geometry[MESH_0] = new CDummyMeshFEM_DG(config);
646  }
647 
648  nDim = geometry[MESH_0]->GetnDim();
649  }
650 
651  /*--- Computation of positive surface area in the z-plane which is used for
652  the calculation of force coefficient (non-dimensionalization). ---*/
653 
654  geometry[MESH_0]->SetPositive_ZArea(config);
655 
656  /*--- Set the actuator disk boundary conditions, if necessary. ---*/
657 
658  for (iMesh = 0; iMesh <= config->GetnMGLevels(); iMesh++) {
659  geometry[iMesh]->MatchActuator_Disk(config);
660  }
661 
662  /*--- If we have any periodic markers in this calculation, we must
663  match the periodic points found on both sides of the periodic BC.
664  Note that the current implementation requires a 1-to-1 matching of
665  periodic points on the pair of periodic faces after the translation
666  or rotation is taken into account. ---*/
667 
668  if ((config->GetnMarker_Periodic() != 0) && !fem_solver) {
669  for (iMesh = 0; iMesh <= config->GetnMGLevels(); iMesh++) {
670 
671  /*--- Note that we loop over pairs of periodic markers individually
672  so that repeated nodes on adjacent periodic faces are properly
673  accounted for in multiple places. ---*/
674 
675  for (unsigned short iPeriodic = 1; iPeriodic <= config->GetnMarker_Periodic()/2; iPeriodic++) {
676  geometry[iMesh]->MatchPeriodic(config, iPeriodic);
677  }
678 
679  /*--- For Streamwise Periodic flow, find a unique reference node on the dedicated inlet marker. ---*/
680  if (config->GetKind_Streamwise_Periodic() != ENUM_STREAMWISE_PERIODIC::NONE)
681  geometry[iMesh]->FindUniqueNode_PeriodicBound(config);
682 
683  /*--- Initialize the communication framework for the periodic BCs. ---*/
684  geometry[iMesh]->PreprocessPeriodicComms(geometry[iMesh], config);
685 
686  }
687  }
688 
689  /*--- If activated by the compile directive, perform a partition analysis. ---*/
690 #if PARTITION
691  if (!dummy){
692  if( fem_solver ) Partition_Analysis_FEM(geometry[MESH_0], config);
693  else Partition_Analysis(geometry[MESH_0], config);
694  }
695 #endif
696 
697  /*--- Check if Euler & Symmetry markers are straight/plane. This information
698  is used in the Euler & Symmetry boundary routines. ---*/
699  if((config_container[iZone]->GetnMarker_Euler() != 0 ||
700  config_container[iZone]->GetnMarker_SymWall() != 0) &&
701  !fem_solver) {
702 
703  if (rank == MASTER_NODE)
704  cout << "Checking if Euler & Symmetry markers are straight/plane:" << endl;
705 
706  for (iMesh = 0; iMesh <= config_container[iZone]->GetnMGLevels(); iMesh++)
707  geometry_container[iZone][iInst][iMesh]->ComputeSurf_Straightness(config_container[iZone], (iMesh==MESH_0) );
708 
709  }
710 
711 }

713 void CDriver::Geometrical_Preprocessing_FVM(CConfig *config, CGeometry **&geometry) {
714 
715  unsigned short iZone = config->GetiZone(), iMGlevel;
716  unsigned short requestedMGlevels = config->GetnMGLevels();
717  const bool fea = config->GetStructuralProblem();
718 
719  /*--- Definition of the geometry class to store the primal grid in the partitioning process.
720  * All ranks process the grid and call ParMETIS for partitioning ---*/
721 
722  CGeometry *geometry_aux = new CPhysicalGeometry(config, iZone, nZone);
723 
724  /*--- Set the dimension --- */
725 
726  nDim = geometry_aux->GetnDim();
727 
728  /*--- Color the initial grid and set the send-receive domains (ParMETIS) ---*/
729 
730  geometry_aux->SetColorGrid_Parallel(config);
731 
732  /*--- Allocate the memory of the current domain, and divide the grid
733  between the ranks. ---*/
734 
735  geometry = new CGeometry *[config->GetnMGLevels()+1] ();
736 
737  /*--- Build the grid data structures using the ParMETIS coloring. ---*/
738 
739  geometry[MESH_0] = new CPhysicalGeometry(geometry_aux, config);
740 
741  /*--- Deallocate the memory of geometry_aux and solver_aux ---*/
742 
743  delete geometry_aux;
744 
745  /*--- Add the Send/Receive boundaries ---*/
746  geometry[MESH_0]->SetSendReceive(config);
747 
748  /*--- Add the Send/Receive boundaries ---*/
749  geometry[MESH_0]->SetBoundaries(config);
750 
751  /*--- Compute elements surrounding points, points surrounding points ---*/
752 
753  if (rank == MASTER_NODE) cout << "Setting point connectivity." << endl;
754  geometry[MESH_0]->SetPoint_Connectivity();
755 
756  /*--- Renumbering points using Reverse Cuthill McKee ordering ---*/
757 
758  if (rank == MASTER_NODE) cout << "Renumbering points (Reverse Cuthill McKee Ordering)." << endl;
759  geometry[MESH_0]->SetRCM_Ordering(config);
760 
761  /*--- recompute elements surrounding points, points surrounding points ---*/
762 
763  if (rank == MASTER_NODE) cout << "Recomputing point connectivity." << endl;
764  geometry[MESH_0]->SetPoint_Connectivity();
765 
766  /*--- Compute elements surrounding elements ---*/
767 
768  if (rank == MASTER_NODE) cout << "Setting element connectivity." << endl;
769  geometry[MESH_0]->SetElement_Connectivity();
770 
771  /*--- Check the orientation before computing geometrical quantities ---*/
772 
773  geometry[MESH_0]->SetBoundVolume();
774  if (config->GetReorientElements()) {
775  if (rank == MASTER_NODE) cout << "Checking the numerical grid orientation." << endl;
776  geometry[MESH_0]->Check_IntElem_Orientation(config);
777  geometry[MESH_0]->Check_BoundElem_Orientation(config);
778  }
779 
780  /*--- Create the edge structure ---*/
781 
782  if (rank == MASTER_NODE) cout << "Identifying edges and vertices." << endl;
783  geometry[MESH_0]->SetEdges();
784  geometry[MESH_0]->SetVertex(config);
785 
786  /*--- Create the control volume structures ---*/
787 
788  if (rank == MASTER_NODE) cout << "Setting the control volume structure." << endl;
789  SU2_OMP_PARALLEL {
790  geometry[MESH_0]->SetControlVolume(config, ALLOCATE);
791  geometry[MESH_0]->SetBoundControlVolume(config, ALLOCATE);
792  }
793  END_SU2_OMP_PARALLEL
794 
795  /*--- Visualize a dual control volume if requested ---*/
796 
797  if ((config->GetVisualize_CV() >= 0) &&
798  (config->GetVisualize_CV() < (long)geometry[MESH_0]->GetGlobal_nPointDomain()))
799  geometry[MESH_0]->VisualizeControlVolume(config);
800 
801  /*--- Identify closest normal neighbor ---*/
802 
803  if (rank == MASTER_NODE) cout << "Searching for the closest normal neighbors to the surfaces." << endl;
804  geometry[MESH_0]->FindNormal_Neighbor(config);
805 
806  /*--- Store the global to local mapping. ---*/
807 
808  if (rank == MASTER_NODE) cout << "Storing a mapping from global to local point index." << endl;
809  geometry[MESH_0]->SetGlobal_to_Local_Point();
810 
811  /*--- Compute the surface curvature ---*/
812 
813  if (!fea) {
814  if (rank == MASTER_NODE) cout << "Compute the surface curvature." << endl;
815  geometry[MESH_0]->ComputeSurf_Curvature(config);
816  }
817 
818  /*--- Compute the global surface areas for all markers. ---*/
819 
820  geometry[MESH_0]->ComputeSurfaceAreaCfgFile(config);
821 
822  /*--- Check for periodicity and disable MG if necessary. ---*/
823 
824  if (rank == MASTER_NODE) cout << "Checking for periodicity." << endl;
825  geometry[MESH_0]->Check_Periodicity(config);
826 
827  /*--- Compute mesh quality statistics on the fine grid. ---*/
828 
829  if (!fea) {
830  if (rank == MASTER_NODE)
831  cout << "Computing mesh quality statistics for the dual control volumes." << endl;
832  geometry[MESH_0]->ComputeMeshQualityStatistics(config);
833  }
834 
835  geometry[MESH_0]->SetMGLevel(MESH_0);
836  if ((config->GetnMGLevels() != 0) && (rank == MASTER_NODE))
837  cout << "Setting the multigrid structure." << endl;
838 
839  /*--- Loop over all the new grid ---*/
840 
841  for (iMGlevel = 1; iMGlevel <= config->GetnMGLevels(); iMGlevel++) {
842 
843  /*--- Create main agglomeration structure ---*/
844 
845  geometry[iMGlevel] = new CMultiGridGeometry(geometry[iMGlevel-1], config, iMGlevel);
846 
847  /*--- Compute points surrounding points. ---*/
848 
849  geometry[iMGlevel]->SetPoint_Connectivity(geometry[iMGlevel-1]);
850 
851  /*--- Create the edge structure ---*/
852 
853  geometry[iMGlevel]->SetEdges();
854  geometry[iMGlevel]->SetVertex(geometry[iMGlevel-1], config);
855 
856  /*--- Create the control volume structures ---*/
857 
858  geometry[iMGlevel]->SetControlVolume(geometry[iMGlevel-1], ALLOCATE);
859  geometry[iMGlevel]->SetBoundControlVolume(geometry[iMGlevel-1], ALLOCATE);
860  geometry[iMGlevel]->SetCoord(geometry[iMGlevel-1]);
861 
862  /*--- Find closest neighbor to a surface point ---*/
863 
864  geometry[iMGlevel]->FindNormal_Neighbor(config);
865 
866  /*--- Store our multigrid index. ---*/
867 
868  geometry[iMGlevel]->SetMGLevel(iMGlevel);
869 
870  /*--- Protect against the situation that we were not able to complete
871  the agglomeration for this level, i.e., there weren't enough points.
872  We need to check if we changed the total number of levels and delete
873  the incomplete CMultiGridGeometry object. ---*/
874 
875  if (config->GetnMGLevels() != requestedMGlevels) {
876  delete geometry[iMGlevel];
877  geometry[iMGlevel] = nullptr;
878  break;
879  }
880 
881  }
882 
883  if (config->GetWrt_MultiGrid()) geometry[MESH_0]->ColorMGLevels(config->GetnMGLevels(), geometry);
884 
885  /*--- For unsteady simulations, initialize the grid volumes
886  and coordinates for previous solutions. Loop over all zones/grids ---*/
887 
888  if ((config->GetTime_Marching() != TIME_MARCHING::STEADY) && config->GetDynamic_Grid()) {
889  for (iMGlevel = 0; iMGlevel <= config->GetnMGLevels(); iMGlevel++) {
890 
891  /*--- Update cell volume ---*/
892  geometry[iMGlevel]->nodes->SetVolume_n();
893  geometry[iMGlevel]->nodes->SetVolume_nM1();
894 
895  if (config->GetGrid_Movement()) {
896  /*--- Update point coordinates ---*/
897  geometry[iMGlevel]->nodes->SetCoord_n();
898  geometry[iMGlevel]->nodes->SetCoord_n1();
899  }
900  }
901  }
902 
903 
904  /*--- Create the data structure for MPI point-to-point communications. ---*/
905 
906  for (iMGlevel = 0; iMGlevel <= config->GetnMGLevels(); iMGlevel++)
907  geometry[iMGlevel]->PreprocessP2PComms(geometry[iMGlevel], config);
908 
909 
910  /*--- Perform a few preprocessing routines and communications. ---*/
911 
912  for (iMGlevel = 0; iMGlevel <= config->GetnMGLevels(); iMGlevel++) {
913 
914  /*--- Compute the max length. ---*/
915 
916  if (!fea) {
917  if ((rank == MASTER_NODE) && (iMGlevel == MESH_0))
918  cout << "Finding max control volume width." << endl;
919  geometry[iMGlevel]->SetMaxLength(config);
920  }
921 
922  /*--- Communicate the number of neighbors. This is needed for
923  some centered schemes and for multigrid in parallel. ---*/
924 
925  if ((rank == MASTER_NODE) && (size > SINGLE_NODE) && (iMGlevel == MESH_0))
926  cout << "Communicating number of neighbors." << endl;
927  geometry[iMGlevel]->InitiateComms(geometry[iMGlevel], config, NEIGHBORS);
928  geometry[iMGlevel]->CompleteComms(geometry[iMGlevel], config, NEIGHBORS);
929  }
930 
931 }

933 void CDriver::Geometrical_Preprocessing_DGFEM(CConfig* config, CGeometry **&geometry) {
934 
935  /*--- Definition of the geometry class to store the primal grid in the partitioning process. ---*/
936  /*--- All ranks process the grid and call ParMETIS for partitioning ---*/
937 
938  CGeometry *geometry_aux = new CPhysicalGeometry(config, iZone, nZone);
939 
940  /*--- Set the dimension --- */
941 
942  nDim = geometry_aux->GetnDim();
943

945  a dummy solver class to retrieve the initial flow state. ---*/

948

959 
960  /*--- Deallocate the memory of geometry_aux and solver_aux ---*/
961 
962  delete geometry_aux;
963  delete solver_aux;
964 
965  /*--- Add the Send/Receive boundaries ---*/
966  geometry[MESH_0]->SetSendReceive(config);
967 
968  /*--- Add the Send/Receive boundaries ---*/
969  geometry[MESH_0]->SetBoundaries(config);

981  if (rank == MASTER_NODE) cout << "Creating face information." << endl;

985  if (rank == MASTER_NODE) cout << "Computing metric terms volume elements." << endl;
986  DGMesh->MetricTermsVolumeElements(config);
987 
988  /*--- Compute the metric terms of the surface elements. ---*/
989  if (rank == MASTER_NODE) cout << "Computing metric terms surface elements." << endl;
990  DGMesh->MetricTermsSurfaceElements(config);
991 
992  /*--- Compute a length scale of the volume elements. ---*/
993  if (rank == MASTER_NODE) cout << "Computing length scale volume elements." << endl;

997  if (rank == MASTER_NODE) cout << "Computing coordinates of the integration points." << endl;

1012  geometry[MESH_0]->SetGlobal_to_Local_Point();
1013 
1014 
1015  /*--- Loop to create the coarser grid levels. ---*/
1016 
1017  for(unsigned short iMGlevel=1; iMGlevel<=config->GetnMGLevels(); iMGlevel++) {
1018

1020  CURRENT_FUNCTION);

1025 void CDriver::Solver_Preprocessing(CConfig* config, CGeometry** geometry, CSolver ***&solver) {
1026

1033

1051

1056 void CDriver::Inlet_Preprocessing(CSolver ***solver, CGeometry **geometry,
1057  CConfig *config) const {
1058 
1059  /*--- Adjust iteration number for unsteady restarts. ---*/
1060 
1061  const bool adjoint = config->GetDiscrete_Adjoint() || config->GetContinuous_Adjoint();
1062 
1063  int val_iter = 0;
1064 
1065  if (config->GetTime_Domain()) {
1066  val_iter = adjoint? config->GetUnst_AdjointIter() : config->GetRestart_Iter();
1067  val_iter -= 1;
1068  if (!adjoint && config->GetTime_Marching() == TIME_MARCHING::DT_STEPPING_2ND)
1069  val_iter -= 1;
1070  if (!adjoint && !config->GetRestart()) val_iter = 0;
1071  }
1072 
1073  /*--- Load inlet profile files for any of the active solver containers.
1074  Note that these routines fill the fine grid data structures for the markers
1075  and restrict values down to all coarser MG levels. ---*/
1076 
1077  if (config->GetInlet_Profile_From_File()) {
1078 
1079  /*--- Use LoadInletProfile() routines for the particular solver. ---*/
1080 
1081  if (rank == MASTER_NODE) {
1082  cout << endl;
1083  cout << "Reading inlet profile from file: ";
1084  cout << config->GetInlet_FileName() << endl;
1085  }
1086 
1087  if (solver[MESH_0][FLOW_SOL]) {
1088  solver[MESH_0][FLOW_SOL]->LoadInletProfile(geometry, solver, config, val_iter, FLOW_SOL, INLET_FLOW);
1089  }
1090  if (solver[MESH_0][TURB_SOL]) {
1091  solver[MESH_0][TURB_SOL]->LoadInletProfile(geometry, solver, config, val_iter, TURB_SOL, INLET_FLOW);
1092  }
1093  if (solver[MESH_0][SPECIES_SOL]) {
1094  solver[MESH_0][SPECIES_SOL]->LoadInletProfile(geometry, solver, config, val_iter, SPECIES_SOL, INLET_FLOW);
1095  }
1096 
1097  /*--- Exit if profiles were requested for a solver that is not available. ---*/
1098 
1099  if (!config->GetFluidProblem()) {
1100  SU2_MPI::Error(string("Inlet profile specification via file (C++) has not been \n") +
1101  string("implemented yet for this solver.\n") +
1102  string("Please set SPECIFIED_INLET_PROFILE= NO and try again."), CURRENT_FUNCTION);
1103  }
1104 
1105  } else {
1106 
1107  /*--- Uniform inlets or python-customized inlets ---*/
1108 
1109  /* --- Initialize quantities for inlet boundary
1110  * This routine does not check if the python wrapper is being used to
1111  * set custom boundary conditions. This is intentional; the
1112  * default values for python custom BCs are initialized with the default
1113  * values specified in the config (avoiding non physical values) --- */
1114 
1115  for (unsigned short iMesh = 0; iMesh <= config->GetnMGLevels(); iMesh++) {
1116  for(unsigned short iMarker=0; iMarker < config->GetnMarker_All(); iMarker++) {
1117  if (solver[iMesh][FLOW_SOL]) solver[iMesh][FLOW_SOL]->SetUniformInlet(config, iMarker);
1118  if (solver[iMesh][TURB_SOL]) solver[iMesh][TURB_SOL]->SetUniformInlet(config, iMarker);
1119  if (solver[iMesh][TRANS_SOL]) solver[iMesh][TRANS_SOL]->SetUniformInlet(config, iMarker);
1120  if (solver[iMesh][SPECIES_SOL]) solver[iMesh][SPECIES_SOL]->SetUniformInlet(config, iMarker);
1121  }
1122  }
1123 
1124  }
1125 
1126 }

1128 void CDriver::Solver_Restart(CSolver ***solver, CGeometry **geometry,
1129  CConfig *config, bool update_geo) {
1130 
1131  /*--- Check for restarts and use the LoadRestart() routines. ---*/
1132 
1133  const bool restart = config->GetRestart();
1134  const bool restart_flow = config->GetRestart_Flow();
1135 
1136  /*--- Adjust iteration number for unsteady restarts. ---*/
1137 
1138  int val_iter = 0;
1139 
1140  const bool adjoint = (config->GetDiscrete_Adjoint() || config->GetContinuous_Adjoint());
1141  const bool time_domain = config->GetTime_Domain();
1142  const bool dt_step_2nd = (config->GetTime_Marching() == TIME_MARCHING::DT_STEPPING_2ND) &&
1143  !config->GetStructuralProblem() && !config->GetFEMSolver() &&
1144  !adjoint && time_domain;
1145 
1146  if (time_domain) {
1147  if (adjoint) val_iter = config->GetUnst_AdjointIter() - 1;
1148  else val_iter = config->GetRestart_Iter() - 1 - dt_step_2nd;
1149  }
1150 
1151  /*--- Restart direct solvers. ---*/
1152 
1153  if (restart || restart_flow) {
1154  for (auto iSol = 0u; iSol < MAX_SOLS; ++iSol) {
1155  auto sol = solver[MESH_0][iSol];
1156  if (sol && !sol->GetAdjoint()) {
1157  /*--- Note that the mesh solver always loads the most recent file (and not -2). ---*/
1158  SU2_OMP_PARALLEL_(if(sol->GetHasHybridParallel()))
1159  sol->LoadRestart(geometry, solver, config, val_iter + (iSol==MESH_SOL && dt_step_2nd), update_geo);
1160  END_SU2_OMP_PARALLEL
1161  }
1162  }
1163  }
1164 
1165  /*--- Restart adjoint solvers. ---*/
1166 
1167  if (restart) {
1168  if ((config->GetKind_Solver() == MAIN_SOLVER::TEMPLATE_SOLVER) ||
1169  (config->GetKind_Solver() == MAIN_SOLVER::ADJ_RANS && !config->GetFrozen_Visc_Cont())) {
1170  SU2_MPI::Error("A restart capability has not been implemented yet for this solver.\n"
1171  "Please set RESTART_SOL= NO and try again.", CURRENT_FUNCTION);
1172  }
1173 
1174  for (auto iSol = 0u; iSol < MAX_SOLS; ++iSol) {
1175  auto sol = solver[MESH_0][iSol];
1176  if (sol && sol->GetAdjoint())
1177  sol->LoadRestart(geometry, solver, config, val_iter, update_geo);
1178  }
1179  }
1180 
1181 }

1219 template <class Indices>
1220 void CDriver::InstantiateTurbulentNumerics(unsigned short nVar_Turb, int offset, const CConfig *config,
1221  const CSolver* turb_solver, CNumerics ****&numerics) const {
1222  const int conv_term = CONV_TERM + offset;
1223  const int visc_term = VISC_TERM + offset;
1224 
1225  const int source_first_term = SOURCE_FIRST_TERM + offset;
1226  const int source_second_term = SOURCE_SECOND_TERM + offset;
1227 
1228  const int conv_bound_term = CONV_BOUND_TERM + offset;
1229  const int visc_bound_term = VISC_BOUND_TERM + offset;
1230 
1231  /*--- Assign turbulence model booleans ---*/
1232 
1233  bool spalart_allmaras = false, menter_sst = false;
1234 
1235  switch (config->GetKind_Turb_Model()) {
1236  case TURB_MODEL::NONE:
1237  SU2_MPI::Error("No turbulence model selected.", CURRENT_FUNCTION);
1238  break;
1239  case TURB_MODEL::SA:
1240  spalart_allmaras = true;
1241  break;
1242  case TURB_MODEL::SST:
1243  menter_sst = true;
1244  break;
1245  }
1246 
1247  /*--- If the Menter SST model is used, store the constants of the model and determine the
1248  free stream values of the turbulent kinetic energy and dissipation rate. ---*/
1249 
1250  const su2double *constants = nullptr;
1251  su2double kine_Inf = 0.0, omega_Inf = 0.0;
1252 
1253  if (menter_sst) {
1254  constants = turb_solver->GetConstants();
1255  kine_Inf = turb_solver->GetTke_Inf();
1256  omega_Inf = turb_solver->GetOmega_Inf();
1257  }
1258 
1259  /*--- Definition of the convective scheme for each equation and mesh level ---*/
1260 
1261  switch (config->GetKind_ConvNumScheme_Turb()) {
1262  case NO_CONVECTIVE:
1263  SU2_MPI::Error("Config file is missing the CONV_NUM_METHOD_TURB option.", CURRENT_FUNCTION);
1264  break;
1265  case SPACE_UPWIND :
1266  for (auto iMGlevel = 0u; iMGlevel <= config->GetnMGLevels(); iMGlevel++) {
1267  if (spalart_allmaras) {
1268  numerics[iMGlevel][TURB_SOL][conv_term] = new CUpwSca_TurbSA<Indices>(nDim, nVar_Turb, config);
1269  }
1270  else if (menter_sst)
1271  numerics[iMGlevel][TURB_SOL][conv_term] = new CUpwSca_TurbSST<Indices>(nDim, nVar_Turb, config);
1272  }
1273  break;
1274  default:
1275  SU2_MPI::Error("Invalid convective scheme for the turbulence equations.", CURRENT_FUNCTION);
1276  break;
1277  }
1278 
1279  /*--- Definition of the viscous scheme for each equation and mesh level ---*/
1280 
1281  for (auto iMGlevel = 0u; iMGlevel <= config->GetnMGLevels(); iMGlevel++) {
1282  if (spalart_allmaras) {
1283  if (config->GetSAParsedOptions().version == SA_OPTIONS::NEG) {
1284  numerics[iMGlevel][TURB_SOL][visc_term] = new CAvgGrad_TurbSA_Neg<Indices>(nDim, nVar_Turb, true, config);
1285  } else {
1286  numerics[iMGlevel][TURB_SOL][visc_term] = new CAvgGrad_TurbSA<Indices>(nDim, nVar_Turb, true, config);
1287  }
1288  }
1289  else if (menter_sst)
1290  numerics[iMGlevel][TURB_SOL][visc_term] = new CAvgGrad_TurbSST<Indices>(nDim, nVar_Turb, constants, true, config);
1291  }
1292 
1293  /*--- Definition of the source term integration scheme for each equation and mesh level ---*/
1294 
1295  for (auto iMGlevel = 0u; iMGlevel <= config->GetnMGLevels(); iMGlevel++) {
1296  auto& turb_source_first_term = numerics[iMGlevel][TURB_SOL][source_first_term];
1297 
1298  if (spalart_allmaras)
1299  turb_source_first_term = SAFactory<Indices>(nDim, config);
1300  else if (menter_sst)
1301  turb_source_first_term = new CSourcePieceWise_TurbSST<Indices>(nDim, nVar_Turb, constants, kine_Inf, omega_Inf,
1302  config);
1303 
1304  numerics[iMGlevel][TURB_SOL][source_second_term] = new CSourceNothing(nDim, nVar_Turb, config);
1305  }
1306 
1307  /*--- Definition of the boundary condition method ---*/
1308 
1309  for (auto iMGlevel = 0u; iMGlevel <= config->GetnMGLevels(); iMGlevel++) {
1310  if (spalart_allmaras) {
1311  numerics[iMGlevel][TURB_SOL][conv_bound_term] = new CUpwSca_TurbSA<Indices>(nDim, nVar_Turb, config);
1312 
1313  if (config->GetSAParsedOptions().version == SA_OPTIONS::NEG) {
1314  numerics[iMGlevel][TURB_SOL][visc_bound_term] = new CAvgGrad_TurbSA_Neg<Indices>(nDim, nVar_Turb, false, config);
1315  } else {
1316  numerics[iMGlevel][TURB_SOL][visc_bound_term] = new CAvgGrad_TurbSA<Indices>(nDim, nVar_Turb, false, config);
1317  }
1318  }
1319  else if (menter_sst) {
1320  numerics[iMGlevel][TURB_SOL][conv_bound_term] = new CUpwSca_TurbSST<Indices>(nDim, nVar_Turb, config);
1321  numerics[iMGlevel][TURB_SOL][visc_bound_term] = new CAvgGrad_TurbSST<Indices>(nDim, nVar_Turb, constants, false,
1322  config);
1323  }
1324  }
1325 }

1387  numerics[iMGlevel][TRANS_SOL][visc_bound_term] = new CAvgGrad_TransLM<Indices>(nDim, nVar_Trans, false, config);

1458 void CDriver::Numerics_Preprocessing(CConfig *config, CGeometry **geometry, CSolver ***solver, CNumerics ****&numerics) const {
1459 
1460  if (rank == MASTER_NODE)
1461  cout << endl <<"------------------- Numerics Preprocessing ( Zone " << config->GetiZone() <<" ) -------------------" << endl;
1462 
1463  unsigned short iMGlevel, iSol,
1464 
1465  nVar_Template = 0,
1466  nVar_Flow = 0,
1467  nVar_NEMO = 0,
1468  nPrimVar_NEMO = 0,
1469  nPrimVarGrad_NEMO = 0,
1470  nVar_Trans = 0,
1471  nVar_Turb = 0,
1472  nVar_Species = 0,
1473  nVar_Adj_Flow = 0,
1474  nVar_Adj_Turb = 0,
1475  nVar_FEM = 0,
1476  nVar_Rad = 0,
1477  nVar_Heat = 0;
1478 
1479  numerics = new CNumerics***[config->GetnMGLevels()+1] ();
1480 
1481  bool compressible = false;
1482  bool incompressible = false;
1483  bool ideal_gas = (config->GetKind_FluidModel() == STANDARD_AIR) || (config->GetKind_FluidModel() == IDEAL_GAS);
1484  bool roe_low_dissipation = (config->GetKind_RoeLowDiss() != NO_ROELOWDISS);
1485 
1486  /*--- Initialize some useful booleans ---*/
1487  bool euler, ns, NEMO_euler, NEMO_ns, turbulent, adj_euler, adj_ns, adj_turb, fem_euler, fem_ns;
1488  bool fem, heat, transition, template_solver;
1489 
1490  euler = ns = NEMO_euler = NEMO_ns = turbulent = adj_euler = adj_ns = adj_turb = fem_euler = fem_ns = false;
1491  fem = heat = transition = template_solver = false;
1492  bool species = false;
1493 
1494  /*--- Assign booleans ---*/
1495  switch (config->GetKind_Solver()) {
1496  case MAIN_SOLVER::TEMPLATE_SOLVER:
1497  template_solver = true; break;
1498 
1499  case MAIN_SOLVER::EULER:
1500  case MAIN_SOLVER::DISC_ADJ_EULER:
1501  euler = compressible = true; break;
1502 
1503  case MAIN_SOLVER::NAVIER_STOKES:
1504  case MAIN_SOLVER::DISC_ADJ_NAVIER_STOKES:
1505  ns = compressible = true;
1506  species = (config->GetKind_Species_Model() != SPECIES_MODEL::NONE); break;
1507 
1508  case MAIN_SOLVER::NEMO_EULER:
1509  NEMO_euler = compressible = true; break;
1510 
1511  case MAIN_SOLVER::NEMO_NAVIER_STOKES:
1512  NEMO_ns = compressible = true; break;
1513 
1514  case MAIN_SOLVER::RANS:
1515  case MAIN_SOLVER::DISC_ADJ_RANS:
1516  ns = compressible = turbulent = true;
1517  transition = (config->GetKind_Trans_Model() == TURB_TRANS_MODEL::LM);
1518  species = config->GetKind_Species_Model() != SPECIES_MODEL::NONE; break;
1519 
1520  case MAIN_SOLVER::INC_EULER:
1521  case MAIN_SOLVER::DISC_ADJ_INC_EULER:
1522  euler = incompressible = true; break;
1523 
1524  case MAIN_SOLVER::INC_NAVIER_STOKES:
1525  case MAIN_SOLVER::DISC_ADJ_INC_NAVIER_STOKES:
1526  ns = incompressible = true;
1527  heat = config->GetWeakly_Coupled_Heat();
1528  species = (config->GetKind_Species_Model() != SPECIES_MODEL::NONE); break;
1529 
1530  case MAIN_SOLVER::INC_RANS:
1531  case MAIN_SOLVER::DISC_ADJ_INC_RANS:
1532  ns = incompressible = turbulent = true;
1533  heat = config->GetWeakly_Coupled_Heat();
1534  transition = (config->GetKind_Trans_Model() == TURB_TRANS_MODEL::LM);
1535  species = (config->GetKind_Species_Model() != SPECIES_MODEL::NONE); break;
1536 
1537  case MAIN_SOLVER::FEM_EULER:
1538  case MAIN_SOLVER::DISC_ADJ_FEM_EULER:
1539  fem_euler = compressible = true; break;
1540 
1541  case MAIN_SOLVER::FEM_NAVIER_STOKES:
1542  case MAIN_SOLVER::DISC_ADJ_FEM_NS:
1543  fem_ns = compressible = true; break;
1544 
1545  case MAIN_SOLVER::FEM_RANS:
1546  case MAIN_SOLVER::DISC_ADJ_FEM_RANS:
1547  fem_ns = compressible = true; break;
1548 
1549  case MAIN_SOLVER::FEM_LES:
1550  fem_ns = compressible = true; break;
1551 
1552  case MAIN_SOLVER::HEAT_EQUATION:
1553  case MAIN_SOLVER::DISC_ADJ_HEAT:
1554  heat = true; break;
1555 
1556  case MAIN_SOLVER::FEM_ELASTICITY:
1557  case MAIN_SOLVER::DISC_ADJ_FEM:
1558  fem = true; break;
1559 
1560  case MAIN_SOLVER::ADJ_EULER:
1561  adj_euler = euler = compressible = true; break;
1562 
1563  case MAIN_SOLVER::ADJ_NAVIER_STOKES:
1564  adj_ns = ns = compressible = true;
1565  turbulent = (config->GetKind_Turb_Model() != TURB_MODEL::NONE); break;
1566 
1567  case MAIN_SOLVER::ADJ_RANS:
1568  adj_ns = ns = compressible = turbulent = true;
1569  adj_turb = !config->GetFrozen_Visc_Cont(); break;
1570 
1571  default:
1572  break;
1573 
1574  }
1575 
1576  /*--- Number of variables for the template ---*/
1577 
1578  if (template_solver) nVar_Flow = solver[MESH_0][FLOW_SOL]->GetnVar();
1579 
1580  /*--- Number of variables for direct problem ---*/
1581 
1582  if (euler) nVar_Flow = solver[MESH_0][FLOW_SOL]->GetnVar();
1583  if (ns) nVar_Flow = solver[MESH_0][FLOW_SOL]->GetnVar();
1584  if (NEMO_euler) nVar_NEMO = solver[MESH_0][FLOW_SOL]->GetnVar();
1585  if (NEMO_ns) nVar_NEMO = solver[MESH_0][FLOW_SOL]->GetnVar();
1586  if (turbulent) nVar_Turb = solver[MESH_0][TURB_SOL]->GetnVar();
1587  if (transition) nVar_Trans = solver[MESH_0][TRANS_SOL]->GetnVar();
1588  if (species) nVar_Species = solver[MESH_0][SPECIES_SOL]->GetnVar();
1589 
1590  if (fem_euler) nVar_Flow = solver[MESH_0][FLOW_SOL]->GetnVar();
1591  if (fem_ns) nVar_Flow = solver[MESH_0][FLOW_SOL]->GetnVar();
1592 
1593  if (fem) nVar_FEM = solver[MESH_0][FEA_SOL]->GetnVar();
1594  if (heat) nVar_Heat = solver[MESH_0][HEAT_SOL]->GetnVar();
1595 
1596  if (config->AddRadiation()) nVar_Rad = solver[MESH_0][RAD_SOL]->GetnVar();
1597 
1598  /*--- Number of variables for adjoint problem ---*/
1599 
1600  if (adj_euler) nVar_Adj_Flow = solver[MESH_0][ADJFLOW_SOL]->GetnVar();
1601  if (adj_ns) nVar_Adj_Flow = solver[MESH_0][ADJFLOW_SOL]->GetnVar();
1602  if (adj_turb) nVar_Adj_Turb = solver[MESH_0][ADJTURB_SOL]->GetnVar();
1603 
1604  /*--- Additional Variables required for NEMO solver ---*/
1605

2417 void CDriver::DynamicMesh_Preprocessing(CConfig *config, CGeometry **geometry, CSolver ***solver, CIteration* iteration,
2418  CVolumetricMovement *&grid_movement, CSurfaceMovement *&surface_movement) const{
2419 
2420  /*--- Instantiate the geometry movement classes for the solution of unsteady
2421  flows on dynamic meshes, including rigid mesh transformations, dynamically
2422  deforming meshes, and preprocessing of harmonic balance. ---*/
2423 
2424  if (!fem_solver && (config->GetGrid_Movement() || (config->GetDirectDiff() == D_DESIGN))) {
2425  if (rank == MASTER_NODE)
2426  cout << "Setting dynamic mesh structure for zone "<< iZone + 1<<"." << endl;
2427  grid_movement = new CVolumetricMovement(geometry[MESH_0], config);
2428 
2429  surface_movement = new CSurfaceMovement();
2430  surface_movement->CopyBoundary(geometry[MESH_0], config);
2431  if (config->GetTime_Marching() == TIME_MARCHING::HARMONIC_BALANCE){
2432  if (rank == MASTER_NODE) cout << endl << "Instance "<< iInst + 1 <<":" << endl;
2433  iteration->SetGrid_Movement(geometry, surface_movement, grid_movement, solver, config, 0, iInst);
2434  }
2435  }
2436 
2437  if (config->GetDirectDiff() == D_DESIGN) {
2438  if (rank == MASTER_NODE)
2439  cout << "Setting surface/volume derivatives." << endl;
2440 
2441  /*--- Set the surface derivatives, i.e. the derivative of the surface mesh nodes with respect to the design variables ---*/
2442 
2443  surface_movement->SetSurface_Derivative(geometry[MESH_0],config);
2444 
2445  /*--- Call the volume deformation routine with derivative mode enabled.
2446  This computes the derivative of the volume mesh with respect to the surface nodes ---*/
2447 
2448  grid_movement->SetVolume_Deformation(geometry[MESH_0],config, true, true);
2449 
2450  /*--- Update the multi-grid structure to propagate the derivative information to the coarser levels ---*/
2451 
2452  CGeometry::UpdateGeometry(geometry,config);
2453 
2454  }
2455 
2456 }

2458 void CDriver::Interface_Preprocessing(CConfig **config, CSolver***** solver, CGeometry**** geometry,
2459  unsigned short** interface_types, CInterface ***interface,
2460  vector<vector<unique_ptr<CInterpolator> > >& interpolation) {
2461 
2462  /*--- Setup interpolation and transfer for all possible donor/target pairs. ---*/
2463 
2464  for (auto target = 0u; target < nZone; target++) {
2465 
2466  for (auto donor = 0u; donor < nZone; donor++) {
2467 
2468  /*--- Aliases to make code less verbose. ---*/
2469  auto& interface_type = interface_types[donor][target];
2470 
2471  if (donor == target) {
2472  interface_type = ZONES_ARE_EQUAL;
2473  continue;
2474  }
2475  interface_type = NO_TRANSFER;
2476 
2477  /*--- If there is a common interface setup the interpolation and transfer. ---*/
2478 
2479  if (!CInterpolator::CheckZonesInterface(config[donor], config[target])) {
2480  interface_type = NO_COMMON_INTERFACE;
2481  }
2482  else {
2483  /*--- Begin the creation of the communication pattern among zones. ---*/
2484 
2485  if (rank == MASTER_NODE) cout << "From zone " << donor << " to zone " << target << ":" << endl;
2486 
2487  /*--- Setup the interpolation. ---*/
2488 
2489  interpolation[donor][target] = unique_ptr<CInterpolator>(CInterpolatorFactory::CreateInterpolator(
2490  geometry, config, interpolation[target][donor].get(), donor, target));
2491 
2492  /*--- The type of variables transferred depends on the donor/target physics. ---*/
2493 
2494  const bool heat_target = config[target]->GetHeatProblem();
2495  const bool fluid_target = config[target]->GetFluidProblem();
2496  const bool structural_target = config[target]->GetStructuralProblem();
2497 
2498  const bool heat_donor = config[donor]->GetHeatProblem();
2499  const bool fluid_donor = config[donor]->GetFluidProblem();
2500  const bool structural_donor = config[donor]->GetStructuralProblem();
2501 
2502  /*--- Initialize the appropriate transfer strategy. ---*/
2503 
2504  if (rank == MASTER_NODE) cout << " Transferring ";
2505 
2506  if (fluid_donor && structural_target) {
2507  interface_type = FLOW_TRACTION;
2508  auto nConst = 2;
2509  bool conservative = config[target]->GetConservativeInterpolation();
2510  if(!config[ZONE_0]->GetDiscrete_Adjoint()) {
2511  interface[donor][target] = new CFlowTractionInterface(nDim, nConst, config[donor], conservative);
2512  } else {
2513  interface[donor][target] = new CDiscAdjFlowTractionInterface(nDim, nConst, config[donor], conservative);
2514  }
2515  if (rank == MASTER_NODE) cout << "fluid " << (conservative? "forces." : "tractions.") << endl;
2516  }
2517  else if (structural_donor && (fluid_target || heat_target)) {
2518  if (solver_container[target][INST_0][MESH_0][MESH_SOL] == nullptr) {
2519  SU2_MPI::Error("Mesh deformation was not correctly specified for the fluid/heat zone.\n"
2520  "Use DEFORM_MESH=YES, and setup MARKER_DEFORM_MESH=(...)", CURRENT_FUNCTION);
2521  }
2522  interface_type = BOUNDARY_DISPLACEMENTS;
2523  if (!config[donor]->GetTime_Domain()) interface[donor][target] = new CDisplacementsInterface(nDim, 0);
2524  else interface[donor][target] = new CDisplacementsInterface(2*nDim, 0);
2525  if (rank == MASTER_NODE) cout << "boundary displacements from the structural solver." << endl;
2526  }
2527  else if (fluid_donor && fluid_target) {
2528  interface_type = SLIDING_INTERFACE;
2529  auto nVar = solver[donor][INST_0][MESH_0][FLOW_SOL]->GetnPrimVar();
2530  interface[donor][target] = new CSlidingInterface(nVar, 0);
2531  if (rank == MASTER_NODE) cout << "sliding interface." << endl;
2532  }
2533  else if (heat_donor || heat_target) {
2534  if (heat_donor && heat_target)
2535  SU2_MPI::Error("Conjugate heat transfer between solids is not implemented.", CURRENT_FUNCTION);
2536 
2537  const auto fluidZone = heat_target? donor : target;
2538 
2539  if (config[fluidZone]->GetEnergy_Equation() || (config[fluidZone]->GetKind_Regime() == ENUM_REGIME::COMPRESSIBLE))
2540  interface_type = heat_target? CONJUGATE_HEAT_FS : CONJUGATE_HEAT_SF;
2541  else if (config[fluidZone]->GetWeakly_Coupled_Heat())
2542  interface_type = heat_target? CONJUGATE_HEAT_WEAKLY_FS : CONJUGATE_HEAT_WEAKLY_SF;
2543  else
2544  interface_type = NO_TRANSFER;
2545 
2546  if (interface_type != NO_TRANSFER) {
2547  auto nVar = 4;
2548  interface[donor][target] = new CConjugateHeatInterface(nVar, 0);
2549  if (rank == MASTER_NODE) cout << "conjugate heat variables." << endl;
2550  }
2551  else {
2552  if (rank == MASTER_NODE) cout << "NO heat variables." << endl;
2553  }
2554  }
2555  else {
2556  if (solver[donor][INST_0][MESH_0][FLOW_SOL] == nullptr)
2557  SU2_MPI::Error("Could not determine the number of variables for transfer.", CURRENT_FUNCTION);
2558 
2559  auto nVar = solver[donor][INST_0][MESH_0][FLOW_SOL]->GetnVar();
2560  interface_type = CONSERVATIVE_VARIABLES;
2561  interface[donor][target] = new CConservativeVarsInterface(nVar, 0);
2562  if (rank == MASTER_NODE) cout << "generic conservative variables." << endl;
2563  }
2564  }
2565 
2566  /*--- Mixing plane for turbo machinery applications. ---*/
2567 
2568  if (config[donor]->GetBoolMixingPlaneInterface()) {
2569  interface_type = MIXING_PLANE;
2570  auto nVar = solver[donor][INST_0][MESH_0][FLOW_SOL]->GetnVar();
2571  interface[donor][target] = new CMixingPlaneInterface(nVar, 0);
2572  if (rank == MASTER_NODE) {
2573  cout << "Set mixing-plane interface from donor zone "
2574  << donor << " to target zone " << target << "." << endl;
2575  }
2576  }
2577 
2578  }
2579 
2580  }

2584 void CDriver::StaticMesh_Preprocessing(const CConfig *config, CGeometry** geometry){
2585 
2586  unsigned short iMGlevel, iMGfine;
2587  unsigned short Kind_Grid_Movement;
2588 
2589  unsigned short iZone = config->GetiZone();
2590 
2591  Kind_Grid_Movement = config->GetKind_GridMovement();
2592 
2593  if (!fem_solver) {
2594 
2595  switch (Kind_Grid_Movement) {
2596 
2597  case ROTATING_FRAME:
2598 
2599  /*--- Steadily rotating frame: set the grid velocities just once
2600  before the first iteration flow solver. ---*/
2601 
2602  if (rank == MASTER_NODE) {
2603  cout << endl << " Setting rotating frame grid velocities";
2604  cout << " for zone " << iZone << "." << endl;
2605  }
2606 
2607  /*--- Set the grid velocities on all multigrid levels for a steadily
2608  rotating reference frame. ---*/
2609 
2610  for (iMGlevel = 0; iMGlevel <= config_container[ZONE_0]->GetnMGLevels(); iMGlevel++){
2611  geometry[iMGlevel]->SetRotationalVelocity(config, true);
2612  geometry[iMGlevel]->SetShroudVelocity(config);
2613  }
2614 
2615  break;
2616 
2617  case STEADY_TRANSLATION:
2618 
2619  /*--- Set the translational velocity and hold the grid fixed during
2620  the calculation (similar to rotating frame, but there is no extra
2621  source term for translation). ---*/
2622 
2623  if (rank == MASTER_NODE)
2624  cout << endl << " Setting translational grid velocities." << endl;
2625 
2626  /*--- Set the translational velocity on all grid levels. ---*/
2627 
2628  for (iMGlevel = 0; iMGlevel <= config_container[ZONE_0]->GetnMGLevels(); iMGlevel++)
2629  geometry_container[iZone][INST_0][iMGlevel]->SetTranslationalVelocity(config, true);
2630 
2631  break;
2632 
2633  default:
2634  break;
2635  }
2636 
2637  if (config->GetnMarker_Moving() > 0) {
2638 
2639  /*--- Fixed wall velocities: set the grid velocities only one time
2640  before the first iteration flow solver. ---*/
2641  if (rank == MASTER_NODE)
2642  cout << endl << " Setting the moving wall velocities." << endl;
2643 
2644  geometry[MESH_0]->SetWallVelocity(config, true);
2645 
2646  /*--- Update the grid velocities on the coarser multigrid levels after
2647  setting the moving wall velocities for the finest mesh. ---*/
2648  for (iMGlevel = 1; iMGlevel <= config->GetnMGLevels(); iMGlevel++){
2649  iMGfine = iMGlevel-1;
2650  geometry[iMGlevel]->SetRestricted_GridVelocity(geometry[iMGfine]);
2651  }
2652  }
2653  } else {
2654 
2655  /*--- Carry out a dynamic cast to CMeshFEM_DG, such that it is not needed to
2656  define all virtual functions in the base class CGeometry. ---*/
2657  CMeshFEM_DG *DGMesh = dynamic_cast<CMeshFEM_DG *>(geometry[MESH_0]);
2658 
2659  /*--- Initialize the static mesh movement, if necessary. ---*/
2660  const unsigned short Kind_Grid_Movement = config->GetKind_GridMovement();
2661  const bool initStaticMovement = (config->GetGrid_Movement() &&
2662  (Kind_Grid_Movement == MOVING_WALL ||
2663  Kind_Grid_Movement == ROTATING_FRAME ||
2664  Kind_Grid_Movement == STEADY_TRANSLATION));
2665 
2666  if(initStaticMovement){
2667  if (rank == MASTER_NODE) cout << "Initialize Static Mesh Movement" << endl;
2668  DGMesh->InitStaticMeshMovement(config, Kind_Grid_Movement, iZone);
2669  }
2670  }
2671

2759  geometry[iZone][INST_0][MESH_0]->SetAvgTurboValue(config[iZone],iZone, OUTFLOW, true);

2845 void CDriver::Print_DirectResidual(RECORDING kind_recording) {
2846 
2847  if (!(rank == MASTER_NODE && kind_recording == RECORDING::SOLUTION_VARIABLES)) return;
2848 
2849  const bool multizone = config_container[ZONE_0]->GetMultizone_Problem();
2850 
2851  /*--- Helper lambda func to return lenghty [iVar][iZone] string. ---*/
2852  auto iVar_iZone2string = [&](unsigned short ivar, unsigned short izone) {
2853  if (multizone)
2854  return "[" + std::to_string(ivar) + "][" + std::to_string(izone) + "]";
2855  else
2856  return "[" + std::to_string(ivar) + "]";
2857  };
2858 
2859  /*--- Print residuals in the first iteration ---*/
2860 
2861  const unsigned short fieldWidth = 15;
2862  PrintingToolbox::CTablePrinter RMSTable(&std::cout);
2863  RMSTable.SetPrecision(config_container[ZONE_0]->GetOutput_Precision());
2864 
2865  /*--- The CTablePrinter requires two sweeps:
2866  *--- 0. Add the colum names (addVals=0=false) plus CTablePrinter.PrintHeader()
2867  *--- 1. Add the RMS-residual values (addVals=1=true) plus CTablePrinter.PrintFooter() ---*/
2868  for (int addVals = 0; addVals < 2; addVals++) {
2869 
2870  for (unsigned short iZone = 0; iZone < nZone; iZone++) {
2871 
2872  auto solvers = solver_container[iZone][INST_0][MESH_0];
2873  auto configs = config_container[iZone];
2874 
2875  /*--- Note: the FEM-Flow solvers are availalbe for disc. adjoint runs only for SingleZone. ---*/
2876  if (configs->GetFluidProblem() || configs->GetFEMSolver()) {
2877 
2878  for (unsigned short iVar = 0; iVar < solvers[FLOW_SOL]->GetnVar(); iVar++) {
2879  if (!addVals)
2880  RMSTable.AddColumn("rms_Flow" + iVar_iZone2string(iVar, iZone), fieldWidth);
2881  else
2882  RMSTable << log10(solvers[FLOW_SOL]->GetRes_RMS(iVar));
2883  }
2884 
2885  if (configs->GetKind_Turb_Model() != TURB_MODEL::NONE && !configs->GetFrozen_Visc_Disc()) {
2886  for (unsigned short iVar = 0; iVar < solvers[TURB_SOL]->GetnVar(); iVar++) {
2887  if (!addVals)
2888  RMSTable.AddColumn("rms_Turb" + iVar_iZone2string(iVar, iZone), fieldWidth);
2889  else
2890  RMSTable << log10(solvers[TURB_SOL]->GetRes_RMS(iVar));
2891  }
2892  }
2893 
2894  if (configs->GetKind_Species_Model() != SPECIES_MODEL::NONE) {
2895  for (unsigned short iVar = 0; iVar < solvers[SPECIES_SOL]->GetnVar(); iVar++) {
2896  if (!addVals)
2897  RMSTable.AddColumn("rms_Spec" + iVar_iZone2string(iVar, iZone), fieldWidth);
2898  else
2899  RMSTable << log10(solvers[SPECIES_SOL]->GetRes_RMS(iVar));
2900  }
2901  }
2902 
2903  if (!multizone && configs->GetWeakly_Coupled_Heat()){
2904  if (!addVals) RMSTable.AddColumn("rms_Heat" + iVar_iZone2string(0, iZone), fieldWidth);
2905  else RMSTable << log10(solvers[HEAT_SOL]->GetRes_RMS(0));
2906  }
2907 
2908  if (configs->AddRadiation()) {
2909  if (!addVals) RMSTable.AddColumn("rms_Rad" + iVar_iZone2string(0, iZone), fieldWidth);
2910  else RMSTable << log10(solvers[RAD_SOL]->GetRes_RMS(0));
2911  }
2912 
2913  }
2914  else if (configs->GetStructuralProblem()) {
2915 
2916  if (configs->GetGeometricConditions() == STRUCT_DEFORMATION::LARGE){
2917  if (!addVals) {
2918  RMSTable.AddColumn("UTOL-A", fieldWidth);
2919  RMSTable.AddColumn("RTOL-A", fieldWidth);
2920  RMSTable.AddColumn("ETOL-A", fieldWidth);
2921  }
2922  else {
2923  RMSTable << log10(solvers[FEA_SOL]->GetRes_FEM(0))
2924  << log10(solvers[FEA_SOL]->GetRes_FEM(1))
2925  << log10(solvers[FEA_SOL]->GetRes_FEM(2));
2926  }
2927  }
2928  else{
2929  if (!addVals) {
2930  RMSTable.AddColumn("log10[RMS Ux]", fieldWidth);
2931  RMSTable.AddColumn("log10[RMS Uy]", fieldWidth);
2932  if (nDim == 3) RMSTable.AddColumn("log10[RMS Uz]", fieldWidth);
2933  }
2934  else {
2935  RMSTable << log10(solvers[FEA_SOL]->GetRes_FEM(0))
2936  << log10(solvers[FEA_SOL]->GetRes_FEM(1));
2937  if (nDim == 3) RMSTable << log10(solvers[FEA_SOL]->GetRes_FEM(2));
2938  }
2939  }
2940 
2941  }
2942  else if (configs->GetHeatProblem()) {
2943 
2944  if (!addVals) RMSTable.AddColumn("rms_Heat" + iVar_iZone2string(0, iZone), fieldWidth);
2945  else RMSTable << log10(solvers[HEAT_SOL]->GetRes_RMS(0));
2946  } else {
2947  SU2_MPI::Error("Invalid KindSolver for CDiscAdj-MultiZone/SingleZone-Driver.", CURRENT_FUNCTION);
2948  }
2949  } // loop iZone
2950 
2951  if (!addVals) RMSTable.PrintHeader();
2952  else RMSTable.PrintFooter();
2953 
2954  } // for addVals
2955 
2956  cout << "\n-------------------------------------------------------------------------\n" << endl;
2957 
2958 }

2966 void CFluidDriver::StartSolver(){
2967 
2968 #ifdef VTUNEPROF
2969  __itt_resume();
2970 #endif
2971 
2972  /*--- Main external loop of the solver. Within this loop, each iteration ---*/
2973 
2974  if (rank == MASTER_NODE){
2975  cout << endl <<"------------------------------ Begin Solver -----------------------------" << endl;
2976  }
2977 
2978  unsigned long Iter = 0;
2979  while ( Iter < Max_Iter ) {
2980 
2981  /*--- Perform some external iteration preprocessing. ---*/
2982 
2983  Preprocess(Iter);
2984

3050 void CFluidDriver::Run() {
3051 
3052  unsigned short iZone, jZone, checkConvergence;
3053  unsigned long IntIter, nIntIter;
3054  bool unsteady;
3055 
3056  /*--- Run a single iteration of a multi-zone problem by looping over all
3057  zones and executing the iterations. Note that data transers between zones
3058  and other intermediate procedures may be required. ---*/
3059 
3060  unsteady = (config_container[MESH_0]->GetTime_Marching() == TIME_MARCHING::DT_STEPPING_1ST) ||
3061  (config_container[MESH_0]->GetTime_Marching() == TIME_MARCHING::DT_STEPPING_2ND);
3062 
3063  /*--- Zone preprocessing ---*/
3064 
3065  for (iZone = 0; iZone < nZone; iZone++)
3066  iteration_container[iZone][INST_0]->Preprocess(output_container[iZone], integration_container, geometry_container, solver_container, numerics_container, config_container, surface_movement, grid_movement, FFDBox, iZone, INST_0);
3067 
3068  /*--- Updating zone interface communication patterns,
3069  needed only for unsteady simulation since for steady problems
3070  this is done once in the interpolator_container constructor
3071  at the beginning of the computation ---*/
3072 
3073  if ( unsteady ) {
3074  for (iZone = 0; iZone < nZone; iZone++) {
3075  for (jZone = 0; jZone < nZone; jZone++)
3076  if(jZone != iZone && interpolator_container[iZone][jZone] != nullptr)
3077  interpolator_container[iZone][jZone]->SetTransferCoeff(config_container);
3078  }
3079  }
3080 
3081  /*--- Begin Unsteady pseudo-time stepping internal loop, if not unsteady it does only one step --*/
3082 
3083  if (unsteady)
3084  nIntIter = config_container[MESH_0]->GetnInner_Iter();
3085  else
3086  nIntIter = 1;
3087 
3088  for (IntIter = 0; IntIter < nIntIter; IntIter++) {
3089 
3090  /*--- At each pseudo time-step updates transfer data ---*/
3091  for (iZone = 0; iZone < nZone; iZone++)
3092  for (jZone = 0; jZone < nZone; jZone++)
3093  if(jZone != iZone && interface_container[iZone][jZone] != nullptr)
3094  Transfer_Data(iZone, jZone);
3095 
3096  /*--- For each zone runs one single iteration ---*/
3097 
3098  for (iZone = 0; iZone < nZone; iZone++) {
3099  config_container[iZone]->SetInnerIter(IntIter);
3100  iteration_container[iZone][INST_0]->Iterate(output_container[iZone], integration_container, geometry_container, solver_container, numerics_container,
3101  config_container, surface_movement, grid_movement, FFDBox, iZone, INST_0);
3102  }
3103 
3104  /*--- Check convergence in each zone --*/
3105 
3106  checkConvergence = 0;
3107  for (iZone = 0; iZone < nZone; iZone++)
3108  checkConvergence += (int) integration_container[iZone][INST_0][FLOW_SOL]->GetConvergence();
3109 
3110  /*--- If convergence was reached in every zone --*/
3111 
3112  if (checkConvergence == nZone) break;
3113  }
3114

3593 void CHBDriver::SetHarmonicBalance(unsigned short iInst) {
3594 
3595  unsigned short iVar, jInst, iMGlevel;
3596  unsigned short nVar = solver_container[ZONE_0][INST_0][MESH_0][FLOW_SOL]->GetnVar();
3597  unsigned long iPoint;
3598  bool implicit = (config_container[ZONE_0]->GetKind_TimeIntScheme_Flow() == EULER_IMPLICIT);
3599  bool adjoint = (config_container[ZONE_0]->GetContinuous_Adjoint());
3600  if (adjoint) {
3601  implicit = (config_container[ZONE_0]->GetKind_TimeIntScheme_AdjFlow() == EULER_IMPLICIT);
3602  }
3603 
3604  unsigned long InnerIter = config_container[ZONE_0]->GetInnerIter();
3605 
3606  /*--- Retrieve values from the config file ---*/
3607  su2double *U = new su2double[nVar];
3608  su2double *U_old = new su2double[nVar];
3609  su2double *Psi = new su2double[nVar];
3610  su2double *Psi_old = new su2double[nVar];
3611  su2double *Source = new su2double[nVar];
3612  su2double deltaU, deltaPsi;
3613 
3614  /*--- Compute period of oscillation ---*/
3615  su2double period = config_container[ZONE_0]->GetHarmonicBalance_Period();
3616 
3617  /*--- Non-dimensionalize the input period, if necessary. */
3618  period /= config_container[ZONE_0]->GetTime_Ref();
3619 
3620  if (InnerIter == 0)
3621  ComputeHB_Operator();
3622 
3623  /*--- Compute various source terms for explicit direct, implicit direct, and adjoint problems ---*/
3624  /*--- Loop over all grid levels ---*/
3625  for (iMGlevel = 0; iMGlevel <= config_container[ZONE_0]->GetnMGLevels(); iMGlevel++) {
3626 
3627  /*--- Loop over each node in the volume mesh ---*/
3628  for (iPoint = 0; iPoint < geometry_container[ZONE_0][iInst][iMGlevel]->GetnPoint(); iPoint++) {
3629 
3630  for (iVar = 0; iVar < nVar; iVar++) {
3631  Source[iVar] = 0.0;
3632  }
3633 
3634  /*--- Step across the columns ---*/
3635  for (jInst = 0; jInst < nInstHB; jInst++) {
3636 
3637  /*--- Retrieve solution at this node in current zone ---*/
3638  for (iVar = 0; iVar < nVar; iVar++) {
3639 
3640  if (!adjoint) {
3641  U[iVar] = solver_container[ZONE_0][jInst][iMGlevel][FLOW_SOL]->GetNodes()->GetSolution(iPoint, iVar);
3642  Source[iVar] += U[iVar]*D[iInst][jInst];
3643 
3644  if (implicit) {
3645  U_old[iVar] = solver_container[ZONE_0][jInst][iMGlevel][FLOW_SOL]->GetNodes()->GetSolution_Old(iPoint, iVar);
3646  deltaU = U[iVar] - U_old[iVar];
3647  Source[iVar] += deltaU*D[iInst][jInst];
3648  }
3649 
3650  }
3651 
3652  else {
3653  Psi[iVar] = solver_container[ZONE_0][jInst][iMGlevel][ADJFLOW_SOL]->GetNodes()->GetSolution(iPoint, iVar);
3654  Source[iVar] += Psi[iVar]*D[jInst][iInst];
3655 
3656  if (implicit) {
3657  Psi_old[iVar] = solver_container[ZONE_0][jInst][iMGlevel][ADJFLOW_SOL]->GetNodes()->GetSolution_Old(iPoint, iVar);
3658  deltaPsi = Psi[iVar] - Psi_old[iVar];
3659  Source[iVar] += deltaPsi*D[jInst][iInst];
3660  }
3661  }
3662  }
3663 
3664  /*--- Store sources for current row ---*/
3665  for (iVar = 0; iVar < nVar; iVar++) {
3666  if (!adjoint) {
3667  solver_container[ZONE_0][iInst][iMGlevel][FLOW_SOL]->GetNodes()->SetHarmonicBalance_Source(iPoint, iVar, Source[iVar]);
3668  }
3669  else {
3670  solver_container[ZONE_0][iInst][iMGlevel][ADJFLOW_SOL]->GetNodes()->SetHarmonicBalance_Source(iPoint, iVar, Source[iVar]);
3671  }
3672  }
3673 
3674  }
3675  }
3676  }
3677 
3678  /*--- Source term for a turbulence model ---*/
3679  if (config_container[ZONE_0]->GetKind_Solver() == MAIN_SOLVER::RANS) {
3680 
3681  /*--- Extra variables needed if we have a turbulence model. ---*/
3682  unsigned short nVar_Turb = solver_container[ZONE_0][INST_0][MESH_0][TURB_SOL]->GetnVar();
3683  su2double *U_Turb = new su2double[nVar_Turb];
3684  su2double *Source_Turb = new su2double[nVar_Turb];
3685 
3686  /*--- Loop over only the finest mesh level (turbulence is always solved
3687  on the original grid only). ---*/
3688  for (iPoint = 0; iPoint < geometry_container[ZONE_0][INST_0][MESH_0]->GetnPoint(); iPoint++) {
3689  for (iVar = 0; iVar < nVar_Turb; iVar++) Source_Turb[iVar] = 0.0;
3690  for (jInst = 0; jInst < nInstHB; jInst++) {
3691 
3692  /*--- Retrieve solution at this node in current zone ---*/
3693  for (iVar = 0; iVar < nVar_Turb; iVar++) {
3694  U_Turb[iVar] = solver_container[ZONE_0][jInst][MESH_0][TURB_SOL]->GetNodes()->GetSolution(iPoint, iVar);
3695  Source_Turb[iVar] += U_Turb[iVar]*D[iInst][jInst];
3696  }
3697  }
3698 
3699  /*--- Store sources for current iZone ---*/
3700  for (iVar = 0; iVar < nVar_Turb; iVar++)
3701  solver_container[ZONE_0][iInst][MESH_0][TURB_SOL]->GetNodes()->SetHarmonicBalance_Source(iPoint, iVar, Source_Turb[iVar]);
3702  }
3703 
3704  delete [] U_Turb;
3705  delete [] Source_Turb;
3706  }
3707 
3708  delete [] Source;
3709  delete [] U;
3710  delete [] U_old;
3711  delete [] Psi;
3712  delete [] Psi_old;
3713

3716 void CHBDriver::StabilizeHarmonicBalance() {
3717 
3718  unsigned short i, j, k, iVar, iInst, jInst, iMGlevel;
3719  unsigned short nVar = solver_container[ZONE_0][INST_0][MESH_0][FLOW_SOL]->GetnVar();
3720  unsigned long iPoint;
3721  bool adjoint = (config_container[ZONE_0]->GetContinuous_Adjoint());
3722 
3723  /*--- Retrieve values from the config file ---*/
3724  su2double *Source = new su2double[nInstHB];
3725  su2double *Source_old = new su2double[nInstHB];
3726  su2double Delta;
3727 
3728  su2double **Pinv = new su2double*[nInstHB];
3729  su2double **P = new su2double*[nInstHB];
3730  for (iInst = 0; iInst < nInstHB; iInst++) {
3731  Pinv[iInst] = new su2double[nInstHB];
3732  P[iInst] = new su2double[nInstHB];
3733  }
3734 
3735  /*--- Loop over all grid levels ---*/
3736  for (iMGlevel = 0; iMGlevel <= config_container[ZONE_0]->GetnMGLevels(); iMGlevel++) {
3737 
3738  /*--- Loop over each node in the volume mesh ---*/
3739  for (iPoint = 0; iPoint < geometry_container[ZONE_0][INST_0][iMGlevel]->GetnPoint(); iPoint++) {
3740 
3741  /*--- Get time step for current node ---*/
3742  Delta = solver_container[ZONE_0][INST_0][iMGlevel][FLOW_SOL]->GetNodes()->GetDelta_Time(iPoint);
3743 
3744  /*--- Setup stabilization matrix for this node ---*/
3745  for (iInst = 0; iInst < nInstHB; iInst++) {
3746  for (jInst = 0; jInst < nInstHB; jInst++) {
3747  if (jInst == iInst ) {
3748  Pinv[iInst][jInst] = 1.0 + Delta*D[iInst][jInst];
3749  }
3750  else {
3751  Pinv[iInst][jInst] = Delta*D[iInst][jInst];
3752  }
3753  }
3754  }
3755 
3756  /*--- Invert stabilization matrix Pinv with Gauss elimination---*/
3757 
3758  /*-- A temporary matrix to hold the inverse, dynamically allocated ---*/
3759  su2double **temp = new su2double*[nInstHB];
3760  for (i = 0; i < nInstHB; i++) {
3761  temp[i] = new su2double[2 * nInstHB];
3762  }
3763 
3764  /*--- Copy the desired matrix into the temporary matrix ---*/
3765  for (i = 0; i < nInstHB; i++) {
3766  for (j = 0; j < nInstHB; j++) {
3767  temp[i][j] = Pinv[i][j];
3768  temp[i][nInstHB + j] = 0;
3769  }
3770  temp[i][nInstHB + i] = 1;
3771  }
3772 
3773  su2double max_val;
3774  unsigned short max_idx;
3775 
3776  /*--- Pivot each column such that the largest number possible divides the other rows ---*/
3777  for (k = 0; k < nInstHB - 1; k++) {
3778  max_idx = k;
3779  max_val = abs(temp[k][k]);
3780  /*--- Find the largest value (pivot) in the column ---*/
3781  for (j = k; j < nInstHB; j++) {
3782  if (abs(temp[j][k]) > max_val) {
3783  max_idx = j;
3784  max_val = abs(temp[j][k]);
3785  }
3786  }
3787 
3788  /*--- Move the row with the highest value up ---*/
3789  for (j = 0; j < (nInstHB * 2); j++) {
3790  su2double d = temp[k][j];
3791  temp[k][j] = temp[max_idx][j];
3792  temp[max_idx][j] = d;
3793  }
3794  /*--- Subtract the moved row from all other rows ---*/
3795  for (i = k + 1; i < nInstHB; i++) {
3796  su2double c = temp[i][k] / temp[k][k];
3797  for (j = 0; j < (nInstHB * 2); j++) {
3798  temp[i][j] = temp[i][j] - temp[k][j] * c;
3799  }
3800  }
3801  }
3802 
3803  /*--- Back-substitution ---*/
3804  for (k = nInstHB - 1; k > 0; k--) {
3805  if (temp[k][k] != su2double(0.0)) {
3806  for (int i = k - 1; i > -1; i--) {
3807  su2double c = temp[i][k] / temp[k][k];
3808  for (j = 0; j < (nInstHB * 2); j++) {
3809  temp[i][j] = temp[i][j] - temp[k][j] * c;
3810  }
3811  }
3812  }
3813  }
3814 
3815  /*--- Normalize the inverse ---*/
3816  for (i = 0; i < nInstHB; i++) {
3817  su2double c = temp[i][i];
3818  for (j = 0; j < nInstHB; j++) {
3819  temp[i][j + nInstHB] = temp[i][j + nInstHB] / c;
3820  }
3821  }
3822 
3823  /*--- Copy the inverse back to the main program flow ---*/
3824  for (i = 0; i < nInstHB; i++) {
3825  for (j = 0; j < nInstHB; j++) {
3826  P[i][j] = temp[i][j + nInstHB];
3827  }
3828  }
3829 
3830  /*--- Delete dynamic template ---*/
3831  for (iInst = 0; iInst < nInstHB; iInst++) {
3832  delete[] temp[iInst];
3833  }
3834  delete[] temp;
3835 
3836  /*--- Loop through variables to precondition ---*/
3837  for (iVar = 0; iVar < nVar; iVar++) {
3838 
3839  /*--- Get current source terms (not yet preconditioned) and zero source array to prepare preconditioning ---*/
3840  for (iInst = 0; iInst < nInstHB; iInst++) {
3841  Source_old[iInst] = solver_container[ZONE_0][iInst][iMGlevel][FLOW_SOL]->GetNodes()->GetHarmonicBalance_Source(iPoint, iVar);
3842  Source[iInst] = 0;
3843  }
3844 
3845  /*--- Step through columns ---*/
3846  for (iInst = 0; iInst < nInstHB; iInst++) {
3847  for (jInst = 0; jInst < nInstHB; jInst++) {
3848  Source[iInst] += P[iInst][jInst]*Source_old[jInst];
3849  }
3850 
3851  /*--- Store updated source terms for current node ---*/
3852  if (!adjoint) {
3853  solver_container[ZONE_0][iInst][iMGlevel][FLOW_SOL]->GetNodes()->SetHarmonicBalance_Source(iPoint, iVar, Source[iInst]);
3854  }
3855  else {
3856  solver_container[ZONE_0][iInst][iMGlevel][ADJFLOW_SOL]->GetNodes()->SetHarmonicBalance_Source(iPoint, iVar, Source[iInst]);
3857  }
3858  }
3859 
3860  }
3861  }
3862  }
3863 
3864  /*--- Deallocate dynamic memory ---*/
3865  for (iInst = 0; iInst < nInstHB; iInst++){
3866  delete [] P[iInst];
3867  delete [] Pinv[iInst];
3868  }
3869  delete [] P;
3870  delete [] Pinv;
3871  delete [] Source;
3872  delete [] Source_old;
3873 
3874 }
