3876 void CHBDriver::ComputeHB_Operator() {
3877 
3878  const complex<su2double> J(0.0,1.0);
3879  unsigned short i, j, k, iInst;
3880 
3881  su2double *Omega_HB = new su2double[nInstHB];
3882  complex<su2double> **E = new complex<su2double>*[nInstHB];
3883  complex<su2double> **Einv = new complex<su2double>*[nInstHB];
3884  complex<su2double> **DD = new complex<su2double>*[nInstHB];
3885  for (iInst = 0; iInst < nInstHB; iInst++) {
3886  E[iInst] = new complex<su2double>[nInstHB];
3887  Einv[iInst] = new complex<su2double>[nInstHB];
3888  DD[iInst] = new complex<su2double>[nInstHB];
3889  }
3890 
3891  /*--- Get simualation period from config file ---*/
3892  su2double Period = config_container[ZONE_0]->GetHarmonicBalance_Period();
3893 
3894  /*--- Non-dimensionalize the input period, if necessary. */
3895  Period /= config_container[ZONE_0]->GetTime_Ref();
3896 
3897  /*--- Build the array containing the selected frequencies to solve ---*/
3898  for (iInst = 0; iInst < nInstHB; iInst++) {
3899  Omega_HB[iInst] = config_container[ZONE_0]->GetOmega_HB()[iInst];
3900  Omega_HB[iInst] /= config_container[ZONE_0]->GetOmega_Ref(); //TODO: check
3901  }
3902 
3903  /*--- Build the diagonal matrix of the frequencies DD ---*/
3904  for (i = 0; i < nInstHB; i++) {
3905  for (k = 0; k < nInstHB; k++) {
3906  if (k == i ) {
3907  DD[i][k] = J*Omega_HB[k];
3908  }
3909  }
3910  }
3911 
3912 
3913  /*--- Build the harmonic balance inverse matrix ---*/
3914  for (i = 0; i < nInstHB; i++) {
3915  for (k = 0; k < nInstHB; k++) {
3916  Einv[i][k] = complex<su2double>(cos(Omega_HB[k]*(i*Period/nInstHB))) + J*complex<su2double>(sin(Omega_HB[k]*(i*Period/nInstHB)));
3917  }
3918  }
3919 
3920  /*--- Invert inverse harmonic balance Einv with Gauss elimination ---*/
3921 
3922  /*-- A temporary matrix to hold the inverse, dynamically allocated ---*/
3923  complex<su2double> **temp = new complex<su2double>*[nInstHB];
3924  for (i = 0; i < nInstHB; i++) {
3925  temp[i] = new complex<su2double>[2 * nInstHB];
3926  }
3927 
3928  /*--- Copy the desired matrix into the temporary matrix ---*/
3929  for (i = 0; i < nInstHB; i++) {
3930  for (j = 0; j < nInstHB; j++) {
3931  temp[i][j] = Einv[i][j];
3932  temp[i][nInstHB + j] = 0;
3933  }
3934  temp[i][nInstHB + i] = 1;
3935  }
3936 
3937  su2double max_val;
3938  unsigned short max_idx;
3939 
3940  /*--- Pivot each column such that the largest number possible divides the other rows ---*/
3941  for (k = 0; k < nInstHB - 1; k++) {
3942  max_idx = k;
3943  max_val = abs(temp[k][k]);
3944  /*--- Find the largest value (pivot) in the column ---*/
3945  for (j = k; j < nInstHB; j++) {
3946  if (abs(temp[j][k]) > max_val) {
3947  max_idx = j;
3948  max_val = abs(temp[j][k]);
3949  }
3950  }
3951  /*--- Move the row with the highest value up ---*/
3952  for (j = 0; j < (nInstHB * 2); j++) {
3953  complex<su2double> d = temp[k][j];
3954  temp[k][j] = temp[max_idx][j];
3955  temp[max_idx][j] = d;
3956  }
3957  /*--- Subtract the moved row from all other rows ---*/
3958  for (i = k + 1; i < nInstHB; i++) {
3959  complex<su2double> c = temp[i][k] / temp[k][k];
3960  for (j = 0; j < (nInstHB * 2); j++) {
3961  temp[i][j] = temp[i][j] - temp[k][j] * c;
3962  }
3963  }
3964  }
3965  /*--- Back-substitution ---*/
3966  for (k = nInstHB - 1; k > 0; k--) {
3967  if (temp[k][k] != complex<su2double>(0.0)) {
3968  for (int i = k - 1; i > -1; i--) {
3969  complex<su2double> c = temp[i][k] / temp[k][k];
3970  for (j = 0; j < (nInstHB * 2); j++) {
3971  temp[i][j] = temp[i][j] - temp[k][j] * c;
3972  }
3973  }
3974  }
3975  }
3976  /*--- Normalize the inverse ---*/
3977  for (i = 0; i < nInstHB; i++) {
3978  complex<su2double> c = temp[i][i];
3979  for (j = 0; j < nInstHB; j++) {
3980  temp[i][j + nInstHB] = temp[i][j + nInstHB] / c;
3981  }
3982  }
3983  /*--- Copy the inverse back to the main program flow ---*/
3984  for (i = 0; i < nInstHB; i++) {
3985  for (j = 0; j < nInstHB; j++) {
3986  E[i][j] = temp[i][j + nInstHB];
3987  }
3988  }
3989  /*--- Delete dynamic template ---*/
3990  for (i = 0; i < nInstHB; i++) {
3991  delete[] temp[i];
3992  }
3993  delete[] temp;
3994 
3995 
3996  /*--- Temporary matrix for performing product ---*/
3997  complex<su2double> **Temp = new complex<su2double>*[nInstHB];
3998 
3999  /*--- Temporary complex HB operator ---*/
4000  complex<su2double> **Dcpx = new complex<su2double>*[nInstHB];
4001 
4002  for (iInst = 0; iInst < nInstHB; iInst++){
4003  Temp[iInst] = new complex<su2double>[nInstHB];
4004  Dcpx[iInst] = new complex<su2double>[nInstHB];
4005  }
4006 
4007
